The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 LOOSE CHANGE

 LIC has launched a unit-linked life insurance policy, Money Plus. The minimum premium for this policy is Rs 5,000 per annum under regular premium paying term. If the single premium mode is chosen, the minimum premium would be Rs 10,000. The plan comes with four investment options bond fund, secured fund, balance fund and growth fund. Under the growth option, a maximum of 80 per cent of the corpus will be invested in equities. However, an investor can opt for switching between the given options four times in a year without paying any additional fee. 

 Franklin Templeton Investments has announced a tax-free dividend of Rs 8 per unit in its open-end equity-linked savings scheme, Franklin India Taxshield. The record date for the dividend is January 10. The scheme had declared a dividend in February 2006 at 35 per cent, or Rs 3.50 per unit. The minimum investment in the scheme is Rs 500.

 UTI Mutual Fund has launched two closed-end funds UTI Capital Protection Oriented Scheme (Series I) and UTI Long Term Advantage Fund. The long-term advantage fund is a 10-year closed-end equity-linked savings scheme and the minimum investment in this scheme is Rs 500. 




